-- Argentine debt mediator, holdouts' lawyer arrive for talks -witness
-- By Dan Burns
-- Wed Jul 30, 2014 10:38AM EDT
-- None



July 30 (Reuters) - The lawyer for the holdout creditors in the Argentina debt standoff and the court mediator assigned to oversee talks between the parties arrived Wednesday morning at the scene for the negotiations, according to Reuters witnesses.   (Reporting by Dan Burns; Editing by James Dalgleish)  ((Daniel.Burns@thomsonreuters.com))  Keywords: ARGENTINA DEBT/LAWYER

